1
00:00:04,127 --> 00:00:06,767
Sometimes we went 
with Gurudev

2
00:00:07,924 --> 00:00:10,679
invited to somebody’s house
for dinner.

3
00:00:10,679 --> 00:00:14,529
So Saraswatī Ṭhākur, that’s also there,
but, you know,

4
00:00:14,529 --> 00:00:17,473
Gauḍīya Maṭh gṛhasthas.
I’ve met some of them,

5
00:00:17,473 --> 00:00:21,490
they’re like out of the pages
of Charitamrita purports.

6
00:00:21,490 --> 00:00:24,608
[Chaste Family Man]

7
00:00:24,608 --> 00:00:27,791
People with full temples
in their house,

8
00:00:27,791 --> 00:00:32,185
Deities, four, five āratis 
every day,

9
00:00:32,185 --> 00:00:33,878
they only take prasādam,
 

10
00:00:33,878 --> 00:00:38,962
they do, they have a whole program 
going on in their house.

11
00:00:38,962 --> 00:00:41,441
Like gṛhastha Vaiṣṇava,

12
00:00:41,441 --> 00:00:46,004
even sometimes they’re called
gṛhastha brahmachārīs.

13
00:00:46,004 --> 00:00:49,774
Yeah, which I told about earlier.

14
00:00:49,774 --> 00:00:52,497
When Kṛṣṇa Kṣetra Prabhu
who in Romania,

15
00:00:52,497 --> 00:00:55,960
sometimes we would visit
with this one Indian professor

16
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:58,027
who was teaching Hindi,
and through him 
 

17
00:00:58,027 --> 00:01:02,895
we could have access to his students,
teach Bhagavad-gītā, give classes, whatever.

18
00:01:02,895 --> 00:01:05,716
But we’d cook at his house,
and he was very happy,

19
00:01:05,716 --> 00:01:08,796
I mean, his wife and family 
were back in India,

20
00:01:08,796 --> 00:01:11,281
and we’d show up,
and he’d get all excited.

21
00:01:11,281 --> 00:01:15,263
We’d cook some things for lunch,
and he showed how to make parathas.

22
00:01:15,263 --> 00:01:17,156
And there are different ways 
to make them.

23
00:01:17,156 --> 00:01:21,172
I should show this to Vishakha
because it’s, like, another way

24
00:01:21,172 --> 00:01:27,677
where they end up looking 
like a diamond‒shape or pyramid.

25
00:01:27,677 --> 00:01:30,481
But ’cause when you take a circle
fold it in half,

26
00:01:30,481 --> 00:01:32,562
and again it ends up
being like that,

27
00:01:32,562 --> 00:01:34,587
but there are a few things
you do along the way.

28
00:01:34,587 --> 00:01:37,828
Anyway, he would do this,
so he’d make his part and our,

29
00:01:37,828 --> 00:01:41,706
and he was really happy
to get some association and everything.

30
00:01:41,706 --> 00:01:45,277
And we were in saffron dress 
as brahmachārīs,

31
00:01:45,277 --> 00:01:48,109
and he could probably
pick up some attitude from us,

32
00:01:48,109 --> 00:01:52,316
like, “we’re brahmachārīs”,
and he’s a gṛhastha,

33
00:01:52,316 --> 00:01:54,206
or something like that.

34
00:01:54,206 --> 00:01:56,709
So, he wanted to let us know,

35
00:01:56,709 --> 00:02:01,656
like, I know something
about brahmachārya too,

36
00:02:01,656 --> 00:02:05,806
maybe more than you, boys.

37
00:02:05,806 --> 00:02:11,433
So he was saying, 
“My wife lives in India,

38
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:18,339
and I see her once a year.”
—Uh, yeah?

39
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:25,535
And he said, “Also I’ve had three children, 
and I’ve never seen my wife naked.”

40
00:02:28,197 --> 00:02:33,143
At that point, you know,
it’s just like, “Oh, bub!”

41
00:02:33,143 --> 00:02:35,668
It’s like,
“How do you process that?”

42
00:02:35,668 --> 00:02:38,847
I don’t, I mean, I’m not trying
to put these images in your mind.

43
00:02:38,847 --> 00:02:41,337
[Laughing]

44
00:02:41,337 --> 00:02:46,197
But he said, “I’ve had three
children …” and I believed him,

45
00:02:46,197 --> 00:02:49,012
he said, “I’ve had three children, 
I’ve never seen my wife naked.”

46
00:02:49,012 --> 00:02:55,435
We were just like, “Will you allow us 
to dress like this in your presence?”

47
00:02:55,435 --> 00:02:58,435
[Laughing]

48
00:02:58,435 --> 00:03:01,685
He means to say,
“I did this dharm …,

49
00:03:01,685 --> 00:03:06,233
Bhagavad-gītā again: 
dharmāviruddho kāmo ’smi
[Bg: 7.11.3-4]

50
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:09,433
and that’s, 
and he was for real.

